UBS Cancer Treatment Development Fund Raises $470 Million   
Largest amount of that has been raised for this type of vehicle, known as impact investing   

 






By

Brian Blackstone


Brian Blackstone
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyBrian Blackstone
@Blackstonebrian
brian.blackstone@wsj.com




  April 27, 2016 11:05 a.m. ET





ZURICH—UBS Group AG said Wednesday it has raised nearly $500 million for a fund aimed at investments in developing new cancer treatments, tapping into growing interest in cancer research. The fund requires a minimum investment of around $500,000, and investors have to lock the money in for five years. UBS said the $471 million it raised for the Oncology Impact Fund—nearly half of it from investors in Asia—is the largest amount ever...
  


